As illustrated in the Fig. S2, the addition of La/N-CQDs resulted in a shift of both the cathodic and anodic regions to lower current densities, indicated their impact on both cathodic and anodic reactions. Following the introduction of La/N-CQDs, the corrosion current density (i

                           corr
                        ) decreased from 3.984 × 10−4 A·cm−2 to 6.324 × 10−5 A·cm−2, while the inhibition efficiency (η) was approximately 84.1 %. Additionally, the corrosion potential (E

                           corr
                        ) shifted positively from −0.821 V to −0.796 V (Table S3). These results indicated that La/N-CQDs function as a mixed-type inhibitor, effectively suppressing both anodic and cathodic processes.
